THE court was filled to capacity when nine senior cops appeared in connection with the Marikana massacre. Scores of Marikana residents and Amcu supporters sat in the Rustenburg Magistrates Court in North West yesterday while protesters gathered outside and sang songs directed at the police. The gates of the court had to be locked to limit the number of people in the grounds of the court. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsu8JpSI8CckricCvnmD6iRxujzXxoJWltE89RL8ym2ZZWSGvh7w9C0W9qsriX15ryAZ8nx1It1hzmgkoqewPS-f-dxZkURs5eJ-7ww4jsa77cQ2Uvx-K7gdhyYqzCLNBSIVAadJvKWps6RGAl6tWlmar3RipZxbbEbNR2Zyne5Yf3KVOGmUZudp0a4HWDzANRQCBDZ73N2BGOqBGfxTtI8Q5oVrDQ5-ezR08BNg9JZJgOFPWTU7eBCnpDiO84chTNPe_o17v8hstTWgl_5YUxUvQQ1aKlA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzKjRBo5RwU9GEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
